name: ModerateInjuriesSNOMEDCT
title: Moderate Injuries (SNOMEDCT)
description: This set of SNOMED CT values contains moderate injury diagnoses, developed to be associated with a patient fall
purpose: (Clinical Focus: The purpose of this SNOMED CT value set is to identify moderate injuries that could occur as a result of a fall),(Data Element Scope: This value set may use a model element related to Diagnosis),(Inclusion Criteria: Includes SNOMED CT concepts that represent moderate injuries that could occur as a result of a fall (such as lacerations, open wounds, dislocations, sprains, and muscle strains.)),(Exclusion Criteria: Excludes major injuries (such as large bone fractures, closed head injuries, internal bleeding, and death.) Excludes minor injuries (such as abrasions, small bone fractures.))
